Issues.Body:
Previously, the state `script` was always appended as the last item in the `body` tag. This can result in the state not being available when the Angular application is bootstrap. A workaround for this was to delay the bootstrapping of the application until by using the `DOMContentLoaded` event listener.

```ts
const bootstrap = () => platformBrowserDynamic().bootstrapModule(AppModule);

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', bootstrap);
```

With this change the above workaround is no longer necessary as the state `script` tag is now added prior of any other `script` which guarantees that the state is present prior of the Angular application is bootstrapped.

### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

router

### Description

I'm building an angular micro frontend app that integrates other angular applications. To be a fast explain: When the "child" application integrates with the "parent" they start to work as a singular application (we use module federation to share the angular libraries).

I have a problem defining the base path based on the application that I'm using.
The "gateway" is multi-repo, so the teams are working separately, and we want every time that we go to the specific app path, change the base path, to their angular application to use this particular path.

Note: The "child" app hasn't the root app module, cause the app module root is being created by the "parent". The child is being integrated via a shared module.

Do we have any way to change it?

### Proposed solution

I saw in the Router class that the base path is being set in the constructor, maybe we can have a method to change the base path dynamically based on the injector from APP_BASE_HREF using the useFactory.

### Alternatives considered


    {
      provide: APP_BASE_HREF,
      useFactory: (pl: PlatformLocation) => {
        return this.state.currentApplicationBasePath();
        // return pl.getBaseHrefFromDOM();
      },
      deps: [PlatformLocation],
    }

